    "content": {
      "type": "doc",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2,
            "textAlign": "left"
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Serial comma",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "attrs": {
            "textAlign": "left"
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Use the serial comma. It goes before “and” or “or” in a list of three or more items. It helps distinguish between the last two items.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "attrs": {
            "textAlign": "left"
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Compare these sentences:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "bulletList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "attrs": {
                    "textAlign": "left"
                  },
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "I want to thank my parents, Juan, and Ana.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "attrs": {
                    "textAlign": "left"
                  },
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "I want to thank my parents, Juan and Ana.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "attrs": {
            "textAlign": "left"
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "In the first sentence, Juan and Ana are not the subject's parents. The first sentence contains  three parallel items, so it takes a serial comma. In the second sentence, Juan and Ana are the subject's parents.  The second sentence contains a noun with an appositive, not three parallel items, so it doesn't take a serial comma.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "attrs": {
            "textAlign": "left"
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Consider this overloaded sentence: ",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "attrs": {
            "textAlign": "left"
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "The Resolver builds out the SynTree with information about any required data conversions and discretionary access control security checks, adds column names and notes any underlying relationships with other database objects and passes the more built-out tree, now known as a ResTree, to Parameterized Value Peek.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "attrs": {
            "textAlign": "left"
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "The user must figure out where each parallel item starts and ends. That's a lot of work. The items are the clauses that start with ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "builds out",
              "type": "text",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "italic"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": ", ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "adds",
              "type": "text",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "italic"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": ", and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "passes",
              "type": "text",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "italic"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": ", but understanding that requires some puzzling—and maybe a few attempts. A serial comma would help a lot. (Restructuring the sentence with bullet points would help more.)",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
